here are facts and figures on polands parliamentary and senate 
elections sunday 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
whats at stake of 460 seats in the sejm or parliament 161 
or 35 percent are open to opposition candidates the remaining 
299 are set aside for members of the communist party and its 
allies all the seats are contested except for a national list 
of 35 positions for which the communist coalition selected 
unopposed candidates 
there are 1745 candidates nationwide for the 425 contested 
seats 
