walt disney co and news corp have 
settled a threeweek old 15 billion lawsuit in which the rupert 
murdochcontrolled company accused disney of fraud 
news corps satellite tv company sky television had claimed 
in the suit that disney had failed to meet terms of its agreement 
to launch the disney channel in the british satellite network 
sky television operates four direct broadcast channels sending 
directly from a communications satellite to a dish at the 
consumers home the deal with disney called for it to supply 18 
hours of daily programming 
besides starting a disney channel for the new enterprise in 
england disney also had agreed to help operate a payperview 
service called sky movies according to the suit 
but news corp alleged that disney dragged its feet seeking to 
change the terms of the agreement news corp sought 1 billion in 
punitive damages and 500 million in actual damages in the may 15 
lawsuit 
under terms of the agreement announced late friday sky will 
purchase disneys undisclosed interest in the joint venture and 
sky will continue to license disney films from touchstone pictures 
and its newly announced hollywood pictures production company for 
the next five years 
disney and sky television will continue to discuss terms of a 
possible disney channel but disney is no longer obligated to 
supply the programming and apparently is free to go elsewhere and 
establish a foothold in recently deregulated european television 
murdoch the british communications and publishing mogul has 
said he hopes the sky television service can reach 1 million 
satellite dish customers in great britain and ireland by early 1990 
walt disney studios president richard frank said disney will 
continue to pursue opportunities for establishing the disney 
channel in these key markets 
the lawsuit had said barry diller head of fox inc the los 
angelesbased entertainment group owned by news corp intervened 
and asked disney executives for better cooperation diller worked 
with disney chairman michael eisner for nearly 16 years at both 
paramount pictures and abc 
eisner denied friday that the two men clashed over the issue 
i never had any quarrel with barry and disney never had any 
quarrel with 20th century fox our dealings were always with the 
british subsidiary of news corp eisner said 
the disney chief said he dealt directly with murdoch in settling 
the suit 
